history.text: Hello! Have you ever seen Zootopia?
Yes I have
I love that movie. I think the casting and idea behind the movie was great.
Yeah it was a good kid's movie with a great message behind it.
I liked the fact that Judy was able to fulfill a childhood dream of becoming a police officer even though she was told she couldn't do it because she is a bunny.
Yeah that was really good, I love rooting for the underdog, and I am glad that she was able to fulfill her dream.
I also like Nick and Finnick as well though even though they were hustlers. Nick ended up being a pretty good guy.
Yeah he was a shady character in the beginning, and he had a rough past but he had a good heart.
Jason Bateman really brought life to his character too. Idris Elba as Chief Bogo was awesome even though I wasn't to fond of him at first. He seemed to be out to get Judy.
The actors were great in their roles, and yeah he seemed to as well but his mind was changed when she proved herself.
What was kind of funny was that Judy ended up beating Nick at his own game and blackmailing him to help with the Otterton case.
Yup that was pretty funny, and that is what started the unlikely duo.
The night howlers clue followed throughout the movie.
Yes it did which was pretty interesting.
Also, the recording carrot pen was great. It was a great take on carrots for rabbits!
Haha yes that part was unexpected and awesome!
When they were able to access the traffic cameras and found it where Manchas was going and that he had been captured by the wolves, I didn't expect to see the mayor there at the asylum.
I didn't expect that either, I thought he was a bad guy at first.
In a way he was I guess because he was involved, but he was really trying to help. When Bellwether took over as mayor, I was a little surprised even though she was the assistant mayor before.
Yeah him being a lion was perfect, because of his "pride". Yeah I didn't expect her to be the mastermind haha
Right, that's a good point. It was great that she was behind it all.
Yeah she had her reasons too, too bad she had to do it in a bad way.
When Judy learned that the night howlers were really flowers, I didn't expect her to reconcile with Nick.
Especially of what happened in the past, yeah I didn't expect it either.
Nick had me fooled. I thought he was really going to attack Judy
Me too, I was like "Nooo!"
Yes, it was such a big climax in the movie. Bellwether ended up telling on herself though. That was great.
A lot of surprises during the climax, but that is good, and the ending was good too.
The fact that they were able to hold onto the evidence was a relief. I was glad to see the arrest of Bellwether at the end.
